Claude Roderick "Rick" Koerber, (born Claud Roderick Franklin 1973, Casper, WY), is a Utah businessman and entrepreneur, who was indicted on charges of orchestrating and running a $100 million Ponzi scheme. Charges were initially dropped, but were refiled in January 2017. After the Appeal Court's denial of Koerber's last-minute appeal attempt to stay the trial, the 8-week jury trial is set to begin on Monday, August 21, 2017.
